   "body" : "Initial spike on this, so opening as draft for CI and Concept/Approach ACKs.\r\n \r\n- update `CNodeStateStats` members to be member-initialized with default values or use `std::optional`\r\n\r\n- fix the regressions noted in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21160#discussion_r597832782 and https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21160#discussion_r597831033, and as patched for us in #25176, in the general case for all client software running v24 by always providing `CNodeStateStats` and the `getpeerinfo` relaytxes and minfeefilter fields that are always present in v23 and with the same default values as v23\r\n\r\n- make the `getpeerinfo` field order consistent with its help and with v23, and update the help to remove the no-longer \"optional\" mentions\r\n\r\n- simplify `-netinfo` by removing several null checks that are now no longer necessary\r\n\r\n- improve the -netinfo help to be more precise regarding tx relay behavior -- commit credited to Martin Zumsande who suggested it in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/25176#discussion_r882090128)\r\n",
